article.headline: Nebraska 77, S. Carolina St. 63
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP)Sek Henry had 18 points and Nebraska used a 15-0 run early in the second half to pull away from South Carolina State 77-63 on Tuesday. The game was tied at 36 when Ade Dagunduro hit a pair of free throws to start the Husker run. The streak ended with a Dagunduro alley-oop dunk that made it 51-36 with 13:29 left. South Carolina State (5-6) got no closer than 11 points the rest of the way. Dagunduro finished with 14 points, Steve Harley had 13 and Paul Velander added 12 for the Huskers (8-3). Jason Johnson had 22 points to lead South Carolina State. Jessie Burton had 11 for the Bulldogs and Jason Flager finished with 10 points.
